Label: Fibrinogen
Comment: Fibrinogen is a so-called Acute Phase Reactant, a class of proteins whose plasma concentrations increase or decrease at least 25 percent during inflammation.

Label: FGB (Bβ)
Comment: 'FGB is not alternatively spliced'

Label: FGG (γ)
Comment: 'fibrinogen gamma chain (also termed the γ chain) encoded by the FGG gene'

Label: FGB (Bβ)
Comment: 'the fibrinogen beta chain (also termed the Bβ or β chain) encoded by the FGB gene'

Label: FGA (Aα)
Comment: 'fibrinogen alpha chain (also termed the Aα or α chain) encoded by the FGA gene'

Label: FGA (AαE)
Comment: 'Alternate splicing of the FGA gene produces a minor expanded isoform of Aα termed AαE which replaces Aα in 1–3% of circulating fibrinogen'

Label: Factor XIII A chain
Comment: Catalytically active

Label: Factor XIII B chain
Comment: Not catalytically active, believed to stabilise A chain

Label: FGG (γ')
Comment: 'alternate splicing of FGG produces a minor isoform of γ termed γ' which replaces γ in 8–10% of circulating fibrinogen'
